<!doctype html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>LT Giphy Battle!</title>
    <style>
      * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
      body { font: 13px Helvetica, Arial; }
      form { background: #000; padding: 3px; position: fixed; bottom: 0; width: 100%; }
      form input { border: 0; padding: 10px; width: 90%; margin-right: .5%; }
      form button { width: 9%; background: rgb(130, 224, 255); border: none; padding: 10px; }
      #messages { list-style-type: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
      #messages li { padding: 5px 10px; }
      #messages li:nth-child(odd) { background: #eee; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <ul id="messages">
    	<li>Send a tag (eg. cats) to load a new random image for that tag every ten minutes.</li>
		<li>Or, send the url to an image (starting with http:// and ending in .gif, .jpg, or .png) to keep that image loaded.</li>
		<li>Your image will be kicked off as soon as someone else sends a battle.</li>
		<li>Use /up and /down to vote the current image up or down. A score less than -2 within 10 minutes will reload a new random 		image.</li>
    </ul>
    <form action="">
      <input id="m" autocomplete="off" /><button>Send</button>
    </form>
	
	<script src="/socket.io/socket.io.js"></script>
	<script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-1.11.1.js"></script>
	<script>
	  var socket = io();
	  $("#m").focus();
	  $('form').submit(function(){
	    socket.emit('tag message', $('#m').val());
	    $('#m').val('');
	    return false;
	  });
	  
	  socket.on('tag message', function(msg){
	      $('#messages').append($('<li>').text(msg));
	  });
		
	</script>
	  
	  
  </body>
</html>
